<h2 id="implementation-tips">🛠️ Implementation Tips From Real Deployments</h2>

Based on implementations we've overseen, here's what separates smooth rollouts from painful ones:

**Start with your highest-volume tour.** Don't try to migrate everything simultaneously. Get your bestseller running perfectly, document the process, then replicate.

**Clean your customer data before migration.** Duplicate records, invalid emails, and incomplete profiles cause problems that compound over time. Invest the hours upfront.

**Map your full booking flow before building.** Document every step from discovery to post-tour review request. This reveals integration points and automation opportunities.

**Train guides on mobile access early.** Staff resistance kills adoption. Include front-line team members in testing and incorporate their feedback.

**Set up channel connections sequentially.** Connect one OTA, verify it's syncing correctly, then add the next. Debugging multiple simultaneous integrations is exponentially harder.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Create a dedicated test tour product for experimenting with settings without affecting live inventory. This becomes invaluable for training new staff and testing new features.
</div>

